# EU AI Act Compliance

## Mandatory Labeling
Every AI-generated content output **must** carry this label — no exceptions.

**In-text (draft, bot messages):**
```
⚠️ AI által generált tartalom — emberi felülvizsgálat szükséges.
```

**In PDF footer (via Jinja2 template):**
```
agentize.eu — AI által generált tartalom — {page}/{pages}
```

**In Adaptive Cards:**
```
⚠️ AI által generált tartalom | Modell: {model} | Generálva: {generated_at}
```

## Human-in-the-Loop (Mandatory)
Two approval checkpoints are required before any PDF is generated:
1. **Review Checkpoint** (`interrupt_before=["review"]`) — draft approval or edit request
2. **Final Approval Checkpoint** (`interrupt_before=["approve"]`) — explicit "I have verified" confirmation

Never skip or bypass either checkpoint, even in test/dev environments.

## Audit Trail
Every completed generation must log to `audit_log` collection:
- `user_id`, `tenant_id`, `channel`
- `llm_model`, `llm_tokens_input`, `llm_tokens_output`
- `approval_timestamp` (ISO 8601 UTC)
- `revision_count`

## LLM Generation Temperature
Keep `temperature ≤ 0.3` for TWI generation to reduce hallucination risk. Intent classification uses `temperature=0.1`.
